<div class="dcf-wrapper">
  <div class="header">
    <div class="header-content">
      <div class="tag">Original Research</div>
      <h1>Marsh & McLennan (MRSH)<br/>Intrinsic Value</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">A transparent, two-stage discounted cash flow valuation of Marsh & McLennan using latest {currentYear} actuals.</p>
      <div class="gemini-badge">Compiled by Gemini 3.1</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="container">
    <!-- ═══ THE VERDICT ═══ -->
    <div class="verdict-card">
      <div class="verdict-label">Estimated Intrinsic Value Per Share</div>
      <div class="verdict-price">${roundedIV > 0 ? roundedIV.toFixed(2) : 'N/A'}</div>
      <div class="verdict-vs">
        {currentPrice !== null ? `vs. market price of $${currentPrice.toFixed(2)} (${marginOfSafety}%)` : 'Market price unavailable'}
      </div>
      {roundedIV > 0 && currentPrice !== null && (
        <div class="verdict-badge" style={`background: ${verdictColor}22; color: ${verdictColor}; border: 1px solid ${verdictColor}44;`}>
          {verdictText}
        </div>
      )}
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ KEY METRICS ═══ -->
    <div class="stats-row">
      <div class="stat-card">
        <div class="stat-value">{revenueBase !== null ? `$${(revenueBase / 1e9).toFixed(1)}B` : 'N/A'}</div>
        <div class="stat-label">TTM Revenue</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-card">
        <div class="stat-value">{fcfBase !== null ? `$${(fcfBase / 1e9).toFixed(2)}B` : 'N/A'}</div>
        <div class="stat-label">Free Cash Flow</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-card">
        <div class="stat-value">{epsBase !== null ? `$${epsBase.toFixed(2)}` : 'N/A'}</div>
        <div class="stat-label">EPS (Diluted)</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-card">
        <div class="stat-value">{netCash !== null ? `$${(netCash / 1e9).toFixed(1)}B` : 'N/A'}</div>
        <div class="stat-label">Net Cash</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ METHODOLOGY ═══ -->
    <h2>Methodology: Two-Stage DCF</h2>
    <p>We use a <strong>two-stage discounted cash flow (DCF)</strong> model to calculate intrinsic value. No multiples, no comparables. Just future cash flows discounted to today.</p>

    <div class="method-step">
      <div class="step-num">1</div>
      <div class="step-content">
        <h4>Start with Free Cash Flow</h4>
        <p>Marsh & McLennan generated <strong>${fcfBase !== null ? (fcfBase / 1e9).toFixed(2) : 'N/A'} billion</strong> in free cash flow over the last year. This is real cash the business produces after paying for operations and capital expenditures.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="method-step">
      <div class="step-num">2</div>
      <div class="step-content">
        <h4>Project FCF growth for 5 years (Phase 1)</h4>
        <p>We grow FCF at <strong>{(growthRatePhase1 * 100).toFixed(1)}% per year</strong> for 5 years. This rate is derived mathematically from the historical 5-year CAGR of FCF and Revenue.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="method-step">
      <div class="step-num">3</div>
      <div class="step-content">
        <h4>Calculate terminal value (Phase 2)</h4>
        <p>After Year 5, we assume FCF grows at <strong>{(growthRateTerminal * 100).toFixed(1)}% forever</strong> — roughly matching nominal GDP growth. We use the <strong>Gordon Growth Model</strong>.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="method-step">
      <div class="step-num">4</div>
      <div class="step-content">
        <h4>Discount everything to present value</h4>
        <p>All future cash flows are discounted at <strong>{(discountRate * 100).toFixed(2)}%</strong> — derived from the 10-year Treasury yield of {(treasury10Y * 100).toFixed(2)}% plus an equity risk premium adjusted for MRSH's stable risk profile.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ THE THREE ASSUMPTIONS ═══ -->
    <h2>The Three Assumptions That Drive Everything</h2>
    <p>A DCF is only as good as its inputs. Here's what we chose and why.</p>

    <div class="assumption-grid">
      <div class="assumption-card">
        <div class="label">FCF Growth Rate (Years 1-5)</div>
        <div class="value">{(growthRatePhase1 * 100).toFixed(1)}%</div>
        <div class="rationale">
          Derived from historical growth rates. Marsh & McLennan has demonstrated stable, consistent growth in its brokerage and consulting businesses, allowing us to mathematically extrapolate this baseline over the medium term.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="assumption-card">
        <div class="label">Discount Rate (WACC)</div>
        <div class="value">{(discountRate * 100).toFixed(2)}%</div>
        <div class="rationale">
          10Y Treasury: {(treasury10Y * 100).toFixed(2)}%. We added an equity risk premium of 5.0% to reflect the relatively low volatility and stable cash flows of an established professional services and insurance brokerage giant.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="assumption-card">
        <div class="label">Terminal Growth Rate</div>
        <div class="value">{(growthRateTerminal * 100).toFixed(1)}%</div>
        <div class="rationale">
          Long-term nominal GDP growth is ~3%. A company that grows slower than GDP in perpetuity eventually becomes irrelevant — 3.0% says Marsh & McLennan grows with the global economy.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ FCF PROJECTIONS TABLE ═══ -->
    <h2>Projected Free Cash Flows</h2>
    <div class="table-wrap">
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th style="text-align:left">Year</th>
            <th>FCF ($M)</th>
            <th>PV Factor</th>
            <th>Present Value ($M)</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>Base</td>
            <td>${fcfBase !== null ? Math.round(fcfBase / 1e6).toLocaleString() : 'N/A'}</td>
            <td>—</td>
            <td>—</td>
          </tr>
          {projectedFCF.map(p => (
            <tr>
              <td>Year {p.year}</td>
              <td>${p.fcf.toLocaleString()}</td>
              <td>{p.pvFactor.toFixed(4)}</td>
              <td>${p.pvFCF.toLocaleString()}</td>
            </tr>
          ))}
          <tr class="row-total">
            <td colspan="3">Sum of Phase 1 PV</td>
            <td class="highlight-cell">${pvPhase1.toLocaleString()}</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ TERMINAL VALUE ═══ -->
    <h3>Terminal Value</h3>
    <div class="table-wrap">
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th style="text-align:left">Component</th>
            <th>Value ($M)</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>Year 6 FCF</td>
            <td>${Math.round(fcfYear6).toLocaleString()}</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Terminal Value</td>
            <td>${terminalValue.toLocaleString()}</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="row-total">
            <td>PV of Terminal Value</td>
            <td class="highlight-cell">${pvTerminalValue.toLocaleString()}</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ FINAL CALCULATION ═══ -->
    <h3>Final Valuation</h3>
    <div class="table-wrap">
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th style="text-align:left">Component</th>
            <th>Value ($M)</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>PV of Phase 1 Cash Flows</td>
            <td>${pvPhase1.toLocaleString()}</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>PV of Terminal Value</td>
            <td>${pvTerminalValue.toLocaleString()}</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>= Enterprise Value</td>
            <td>${enterpriseValue.toLocaleString()}</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>+ Net Cash</td>
            <td>${Math.round(netCashM).toLocaleString()}</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>= Equity Value</td>
            <td>${Math.round(equityValue).toLocaleString()}</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>÷ Shares Outstanding</td>
            <td>{sharesOutstanding !== null ? Math.round(sharesOutstanding).toLocaleString() : 'N/A'}</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="row-total">
            <td>Intrinsic Value Per Share</td>
            <td class="highlight-cell">${roundedIV.toFixed(2)}</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ HISTORICAL CHARTS ═══ -->
    <h2>Financial Track Record</h2>

    <h3>Revenue ($M)</h3>
    <div class="bar-chart">
      {revenueHistory.map(r => (
        <div class="bar-row">
          <div class="bar-label">{r.year}</div>
          <div class="bar-track">
            <div class="bar-fill revenue" style={`width: ${(r.value / maxRev) * 100}%`}>
              ${(r.value / 1e6).toFixed(0)}M
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <h3>Free Cash Flow ($M)</h3>
    <div class="bar-chart">
      {fcfHistory.map(r => (
        <div class="bar-row">
          <div class="bar-label">{r.year}</div>
          <div class="bar-track">
            <div class="bar-fill fcf" style={`width: ${(r.value / maxFcf) * 100}%`}>
              ${(r.value / 1e6).toFixed(0)}M
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ SENSITIVITY ANALYSIS ═══ -->
    <h2>Sensitivity Analysis</h2>
    <p>Find the combination of discount rate and growth you believe in.</p>

    <div class="table-wrap">
      <table class="sensitivity-table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th style="text-align:left">Discount Rate ↓ / Growth →</th>
            {sensitivityGrowth.map(g => (
              <th class={Math.abs(g - growthRatePhase1) < 0.001 ? 'current' : ''}>{(g * 100).toFixed(1)}%</th>
            ))}
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          {sensitivityTable.map(row => (
            <tr>
              <td>{(row.dr * 100).toFixed(2)}%</td>
              {row.values.map((v, i) => (
                <td class={Math.abs(row.dr - discountRate) < 0.001 && Math.abs(sensitivityGrowth[i] - growthRatePhase1) < 0.001 ? 'current' : ''}>
                  ${v}
                </td>
              ))}
            </tr>
          ))}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ RISKS ═══ -->
    <h2>What This Model Doesn't Capture</h2>
    <h3>Upside risks</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>M&A Synergies:</strong> Marsh & McLennan frequently acquires smaller brokerages. If integration yields better margins, cash flows could exceed base projections.</li>
      <li><strong>Hard Insurance Markets:</strong> Prolonged periods of rising insurance premiums natively boost brokerage commissions without requiring extra capital investment.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Downside risks</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Macroeconomic downturns:</strong> Reduced business activity lowers consulting demand and insurance coverage needs.</li>
      <li><strong>Regulatory changes:</strong> Changes in fiduciary rules or insurance compensation disclosure could pressure margins.</li>
    </ul>

    <!-- ═══ FAQ ═══ -->
    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <div class="faq">
      <details>
        <summary>Why use DCF instead of a P/E multiple?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">Multiples reflect market sentiment. A DCF models intrinsic value based on future cash generation, independent of short-term market euphoria or panic.</div>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Is this a buy recommendation?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">No. This is an analytical framework. Whether to invest depends on your risk tolerance, portfolio allocation, and conviction in the underlying assumptions.</div>
      </details>
    </div>

